pr_body:
<!--- Provide a short summary of your changes in the Title -->
This PR aims to develop a realtime collaboration system to enable users to work together in real time.

A demo link for features currently implemented is available here -> [Camicroscope Real Time Collaboration - v1.0](https://youtu.be/jT4tpCJrILU)

This PR depends on [caMicroscope PR-531](https://github.com/camicroscope/caMicroscope/pull/531)
and [Caracal PR-113](https://github.com/camicroscope/Caracal/pull/113)

## Summary
Features included:
- In-viewer collaboration (currently limited to annotations/draw tool), using async request interceptors.
- Manage collaboration room in `table.html` and `viewer.html`. 
- Granting and revoking access to rooms
- Role based actions
- Securing sockets connections using JWT
- Video/Voice call using Jitsi Meet

## Motivation
Since the pandemic, most people have switched to working remotely, and this feature would enable them to work remotely.

## Testing
Tested on Windows 10 Home, using 
- Docker Desktop, running on Docker Engine v20.10.6
- Microsoft Edge Version 91.0.864.59 (Official build) (64-bit)

## Questions
### Features yet to implement ->
- Chat window
- Extending collaborations to other features such as heatmaps, etc
- Extending Role based actions
- Cleaning up code and removing comments

### Problems yet to be solved
- Cross client socket communication not working on docker, but is working when setup is done outside of docker.


<!--- Mark a pull request as a draft to signal that it is not ready for review. -->

- Role based actions
- Securing sockets connections using JWT
- Video/Voice call using Jitsi Meet

## Motivation
Since the pandemic, most people have switched to working remotely, and this feature would enable them to work remotely.

## Testing
Tested on Windows 10 Home, using 
- Docker Desktop, running on Docker Engine v20.10.6
- Microsoft Edge Version 91.0.864.59 (Official build) (64-bit)

## Questions
### Features yet to implement ->
- Chat window
- Extending collaborations to other features such as heatmaps, etc
- Extending Role based actions
- Cleaning code and removing comments/console logs

### Problems yet to be solved
- Cross client socket communication not working on docker, but is working when setup is done outside of docker.
